üìò Compliance Audit ‚Äì Session 10
Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA)
Image

Image

Image

üîπ BASIC LEVEL MCQs (10)
1. HIPAA primarily protects:
A. Financial data
B. Healthcare information
C. Network traffic
D. Intellectual property

2. HIPAA applies mainly to:
A. All IT companies
B. Covered entities and business associates
C. Government agencies only
D. Individuals only

3. Which type of data is protected under HIPAA?
A. Public data
B. PHI (Protected Health Information)
C. System logs
D. Source code

4. HIPAA was enacted in the year:
A. 1990
B. 1996
C. 2001
D. 2005

5. Which of the following is a HIPAA objective?
A. Improve coding standards
B. Ensure privacy and security of health data
C. Increase hospital revenue
D. Replace ISO standards

6. HIPAA is best described as a:
A. Voluntary framework
B. Mandatory regulation
C. Security tool
D. Audit guideline

7. PHI includes:
A. Server IP address
B. Patient medical records
C. Firewall rules
D. Software license

8. HIPAA compliance failure may lead to:
A. Only warnings
B. Civil and criminal penalties
C. Improved compliance
D. No impact

9. HIPAA applies mainly in which country?
A. India
B. European Union
C. United States
D. Global

10. HIPAA is MOST relevant to which sector?
A. Banking
B. Healthcare
C. Manufacturing
D. Telecom

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE LEVEL MCQs (10)
11. HIPAA Privacy Rule primarily governs:
A. Network security
B. Use and disclosure of PHI
C. Incident response
D. Encryption algorithms

12. The HIPAA Security Rule focuses on:
A. Physical safety only
B. Administrative, physical, and technical safeguards
C. Financial audits
D. Employee background checks

13. Which HIPAA rule mandates reporting of data breaches?
A. Privacy Rule
B. Security Rule
C. Breach Notification Rule
D. Enforcement Rule

14. HIPAA covered entities include:
A. Hospitals and healthcare providers
B. Hackers
C. Software vendors only
D. End users

15. Business associates under HIPAA are organizations that:
A. Provide medical treatment
B. Handle PHI on behalf of covered entities
C. Regulate healthcare
D. Perform audits only

16. Which safeguard includes policies, procedures, and workforce training?
A. Technical
B. Physical
C. Administrative
D. Network

17. Encryption and access control fall under which safeguard?
A. Administrative
B. Physical
C. Technical
D. Legal

18. HIPAA Privacy Rule gives patients the right to:
A. Modify network settings
B. Access and request correction of their records
C. Delete audit logs
D. Avoid audits

19. HIPAA Security Rule applies to:
A. Paper records only
B. Electronic PHI (ePHI)
C. Financial data
D. Public data

20. HIPAA Breach Notification Rule requires notification within:
A. 24 hours
B. 48 hours
C. 60 days
D. One year

üî¥ ADVANCED LEVEL MCQs (10)
21. HIPAA Titles define:
A. Audit phases
B. Broad purpose and scope of the Act
C. Security tools
D. ISO mappings

22. Title II of HIPAA is MOST associated with:
A. Portability of insurance
B. Administrative simplification
C. Financial audits
D. Clinical trials

23. HIPAA Enforcement Rule deals with:
A. Safeguards
B. Penalties and investigations
C. Data classification
D. Risk assessment

24. Which scenario BEST represents a HIPAA violation?
A. Encrypting PHI
B. Unauthorized access to patient records
C. Conducting risk assessment
D. Applying access control

25. HIPAA requires risk analysis to:
A. Eliminate all risks
B. Identify and reduce risks to ePHI
C. Replace audits
D. Increase compliance cost

26. A cloud service provider handling patient data is considered a:
A. Covered entity
B. Business associate
C. Regulator
D. Auditor

27. HIPAA Security Rule flexibility means controls should be:
A. Identical for all organizations
B. Scaled based on size and risk
C. Ignored if costly
D. Optional

28. HIPAA Privacy Rule violation MOST impacts:
A. Network performance
B. Patient trust and legal compliance
C. System availability
D. Incident response time

29. From compliance audit perspective, HIPAA emphasizes:
A. Tool implementation
B. Confidentiality, integrity, and availability of PHI
C. Software development
D. Network optimization

30. From CCEE exam viewpoint, HIPAA questions MOSTLY test:
A. Penalty amounts
B. Rules, roles, and safeguards
C. Coding standards
D. Encryption algorithms

